The paper deals with the coordinated beamforming design problem for the MISO interference channel, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization problem and proposes approximation methods, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of semidefinite relaxation and first-order approximation techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) categories.
